A Jinkoh Series chest or cabinet adds a substantial and elegant presence to any room. Handsome, uniquely cut Fir wood is complemented with coffered details, crowned pedestal and pediments, gorgeous floral-patterned iron pulls and decorative medallions. Equally at home in a traditional or eclectic setting. Beautiful Aged Warm Oak antique finish.

Crowned with a semicircular arch showcasing a charming ten-segment sunburst, this elegant fir wood mirror features crown molding and pedestal, proud fluted pilasters, and a distinctly island feel. Palm fronds not included

With its sleek Copper surface, “Streamline Moderne” Gold Leaf “speed lines” and glamorous convex-curved Polished Chrome pulls, the Gold Strip Cabinet exemplifies the celebration of rich color, eclecticism and bold aerodynamic ornamentation that Art Deco design stories have been renowned for since the early 2th century.

Art Deco has always been noted for its celebration of velocity and verticality, yet also for its love of color. Both are well represented in our quietly exotic Copper Frame Mirror. The introduction of aerodynamics in the early twentieth century ushered in an era of streamlined objects featuring speed lines as though they were designed in a wind tunnel, and this is echoed with the Mohawk's slick Gold Leaf striping. Perfect for that chic urban adress.

Great design is a statement; not a question. Generously scaled at 66 with a provocative space-age aesthetic, the Pulse Sculpture brings visual cachet to a lofty space or height and drama to a small room. Rich Dark Bronze color story.

Right around the time that uniquely crisscrossed “tensegral” construction was conceived by European Architects to minimize material while adding structural resiliency, the raw aesthetic of urban frameworks became so exciting that no further embellishment was necessary. Introducing our modish Moya Collection Accent Tables: Super hip with their polished concrete tops and Aged Iron color story, the Moya are right at home in any high-concept design space.

attrib__finish: Grey Wood Tone, White Antique Wash

product__description: The Topanga Cabinet is perfect for today’s Modern Bohemian design space. Styled with "farm-found" wood done in Weathered Grey, with Antiqued Brass pulls. Fashionable mixed-media drawer-fronts feature urban, Indo-Gothic, and Art Deco-inspired fretwork, as well as black slate and witty graphic arias. Generously scaled.

The Topanga Cabinet is perfect for today’s Modern Bohemian design space. Styled with "farm-found" wood done in Natural Stain, with Antiqued pulls and soothing Cream facades. Fashionable mixed-media drawer-fronts feature neat Mid-Mod fretwork, as well as black slate and textured fabric arias. Generously scaled.

The Topanga Cabinet is perfect for today’s Modern Bohemian design space. Styled with "farm-found" wood done in Light Grey Wash and fashionable gothic or mandala-inspired fretwork. Nostalgic mixed-media drawer-fronts feature simple mesh, black slate, or Antiqued pulls inspired by vintage library catalogs.

product__description: Drawer fronts are finished in German silver with nail head to make a trend-forward statement.

Our Novae Metal Wall Decor offers the urbo-Industrial look of modern metal sculpture with a future-forward design twist. Showcases machine-etched surfacing, provocative morphographic patterning, and a sleek glazed finish. Stylish Soft Silver with Burnt Sienna color story.

somewhere in the distant center of the universe the massive eruption of a neutron star has begun; its explosively radiating bright Copper center causing a pulse of nebulous concentric rings to blast into the distance. Introducing our Pulsar Series Metal Wall Decor: Because high concept design spaces require high energy enhancements. Perfect to make a bold statement in the entryway. Alluring Bastille Silver color story.

A “luxuriance of imagination” that has spanned centuries, Baroque design is exuberant, grand, and immaculate. Our Triomphe Baroque Wall Medallions feature a quartet of beautifully symmetrical fleur-de-lis surrounded by delicate flower bud banding. Resplendent Champagne Gold with Antiqued White color story. Perfect for a stylish entry stairwell.

Inspired by lavish 1930's Hollywood Regency-style interiors, our Archipelago Wall Decor evokes a gathering of Bright Gold embossed metal “islets” whose milky Jade, Caribbean Blue and Oxblood-glazed center adornments emulate the exquisite banding of genuine polished volcanic agate. #StatementDecor

Industrial Loft-themed design stories encompass two perfectly balanced paradigms: Utility and accidental elegance. Evocative of the silhouette made ubiquitous by early 2th Century French manufacturer Xavier Pauchard, our Acento series Metal Cafe Chair is sturdy, modern and Loft Chic. Contempo Metallic Silver finish. Put this one with a morning au lait' and pretend you're in Paris.

Our Cruzada Stands balance a cool White base with agate-evocative center jewelry and a dynamic radiance of Metallic Gold obelisks. Color stories include: Milky Jade, Cerulean Blue, and Oxblood-glazed. Set of 3.

1930's Hollywood Regency-style interiors were all about unabashedly glamorous ornamentation. Our Regency-inspired Sangreal Box embellishes a beautifully contrastive Jet Noir with Honey Gold color story with an agate-evocative ornamental pull done in a dazzling Caribbean Blue. Fill this one with opera glasses and vintage pearls.

Our Goldplume Wall Decor organizes beautifully crafted metal feathers into subtly rhythmical layers, speaking to ceremonial craftsmanship. Gorgeous Soft Gold with Chalk color story and elegant Jet Noir wood frame.   At home in any sophisticated entryway

The unique diversiform silhouette of our Ascencio Candle Holder lifts light onto the shoulders of eight staggered openwork metal towers; while its hinged design allows for the concentration or extension of soft candlelight. Rustic metalwork offers the look of textured industrial sheeting, completing the design.

product__description: Cactus and sun-scorched desert highway signs just seem to go together. Our Oaxaca Metal Cactus Sculptures express this notion in Modern Abstract using dimpled steel. Complete with blooming flower and clay pot-style base. Rust and Pewter finish with bright Gold nodes. Hip-to-eclectic application.

Cactus and sun-scorched desert highway signs just seem to go together. Our Oaxaca Metal Cactus Sculptures express this notion in Modern Abstract using dimpled steel. Complete with blooming flower and clay pot-style base. Rust and Pewter finish with bright Gold nodes. Hip-to-eclectic application.

With its dynamic triangular frameworks, sleek glass curtain walls and dramatic angular silhouette, the Bank of China Tower is one of the most recognizable skyscrapers in Central Hong Kong; and a shining example of the lively, prosperous message that modern Structural Expressionist architecture seeks to convey. Beautifully hand painted. Stylish Black mahogany frame.

La Tour Eiffel (Eiffel Tower) has graced the skyline of Paris, France since its debut at the World's Fair in 1889. Immediately a target of artistic controversy for its “radical and ghastly” silhouette, it has since become a celebrated global cultural icon and one of the most recognizable structures in the world. Beautifully hand painted. Stylish Black mahogany frame.

Perched high atop a rugged mountain in breathtaking southwest Bavaria, Neuschwanstein Castle is one of the most popular tourist destinations in Europe. Itself a 19th Century romantic interpretation of a Medieval German Palace, it continues to serve as the model for the fantasy castles of today. Beautifully hand painted. Stylish Black mahogany frame.

Chronometers, pulleys, gears, weights. Pendulums, crystals, bells, springs. Oscillators, forks, hands, and chains. It's easy to forget that a clock is technology; yet even after centuries it's still not the main reason we mount one on our wall. Introducing our elegant and stately Aged Copper Wall Clock: With its handsome cursive-stamped face and a silhouette reminiscent of a time-worn antique hour sprocket, the Citadel evokes the classic appeal and inherent wonder of the Age of Progress. Distinctive Aged Copper finish.

situated in Central London's majestic Trafalgar Square since 1824, the National Gallery is one of the most renowned art museums in the world. Sharing its stateliness and early 19th Century elegance is our National Gallery-themed Wall Clock: Features a handsome Roman numeral face, classic pocket-watch design story and a distinctive Polished Copper finish.

searching for the perfect mate for your modern, traditional, or eclectic shelving unit? Check out our Chess Piece Book Ends: A majestic pair of gleaming Polished Aluminum sovereigns, whose generous scale and inimitable mystique bring the perfect endgame for those looking to surround their books with an air as elegant and timeless as the game of chess itself. Ideal for any distinctive office. Or use them as a witty accessory for the gift of a complete series of novels.

Go ahead. Try to resist the warmth and cuteness of our Mango Wood Penguin. You know you want to put this on your desk and talk to it. We want you to. If you need to you can hang a couple of rubber bands from its adorable little Brass beak; but really just…put him there next to the phone. When WE do this WE instantly feel better. Something inside has mended. That is all.

At Dimond Home we believe in “Once Upon a Time,” and once upon a time children played with wooden toys. Cars and trucks and locomotives; and little wooden people. Introducing our Rhinocerous Box: a warm and utterly adorable little Mango Wood repository embellished with a rhinocerous-shaped bust made from a pop of chic, creamy Royal German Silver. Fill it with paper clips! Or just move it along your desk making a growly sound.

Exquisite Renaissance sculpture: Beautifully ornate Gothic tracery: Majestic Medieval heraldry: All have one thing in common: the Quatrefoil. Introducing our Gold Leaf Nested Quatrefoil Accent Tables: Classic “four-leaf” bases of boldly symmetrical overlapping circles emblazoned with a sophisticated Golden sheen; whose slender arms hold aloft their dark, rich, Gold-banded Mango Wood surfaces. Perfect as the elegant centerpiece of the next great conversation. Imagine them adorned with several robust snifters and an illustrated treatise on European castles.

The Amethyst tray balances sleek modern componentry with the surpassing beauty of natural symmetry, placing a gorgeous shock of genuine amethyst opposite precision-cut Polished Nickel. The result is a height-of-style statement piece showcasing discrete depths of Natural, White and Dark Violet crystal. Handcrafted.

Our Organic Cutouts Side Table is what happens when modern sleek and old school masonry converge. Like an ancient rustic wall, irregular openwork cutouts act like loose field stones  bound together by Polished Aluminum mortar. The result is a graceful curved cylinder with a sparkling beveled glass top that allows such details to be appreciated from anywhere in the room. Pair it with a vibrant centerpiece and a stack of good books on urban architecture.

Inspired by the beauty of Fan coral radiating across searock, our Gold Coral Leaf Veins Aluminum Disk continues this season's emphasis on embellishing the geometry found in nature with sophisticated finishes. Variegated shoots of alternating thickness imitate actual coral patterns, while the platter's radial energy lends the impression of movement. As a great refuge and resource, the world's coral reefs have become a symbol of plentifulness. This makes the Eisee a perfect adornment for a lavish dining room sideboard.

Everyone should have a fairytale thicket lurking somewhere in their home, and our woody but contemporary Silvered Sticks Side Table fits the narrative. Magical, authentically textured, intertwining branches reach up to suspend a sparkling glass top while creeping playfully over its edges. An antique Nickel finish lends a cool contemporary look. Use it as a nightstand for a fanciful lamp and a stack of enchanting tomes.

Add a pop of glam to a transitional space with our Pebble series Polished Nickel accent table. Like a cluster of uniquely sized cobblestones shimmering in the moonlight after a rain and then gathered up stereographically, this substantial, impossible-to-ignore piece promises to bring light and heightened interest to any room.

Inspired by the grandeur and quietude of a Buddhist temple, the Spray Bowl's dynamic golden rings evoke the ripples of sound that reverberate from an instrumental gong. Beginning as a single reed-like strand of metal, each piece is hand-wrought and soldered into the shape of a Golden whirlpool that winds its way down to a calming center disk. Bring all three together as an ideal centerpiece for an extended dining table or entryway console.

Design Eclecticism is all about “being multiple,” and boldly so. Introducing our Djembe Series Set of 2 Hammered Metal Stools: Resplendent with their elliptical dimples and burnished Coppery metalwork, the Djembe combine versatile functionality and an Urbo-Bohemian vibe with the look and feel of Afro-Cuban percussion instruments. Perfect as extra seating for that crowd of ukulele-playing guests. Or imagine them as tables in a conversation pit full of low-slung Moroccan pillows.

Evocative of the ripples of sound that reverberate from an instrumental gong, the dynamic concentric rings of our Tam-Tam Collection Baskets summon the grandeur and quietude of an Eastern temple. Beginning as a single reed-like strand of metal, each piece is hand-wrought and soldered into the shape of a bright Coppery whirlpool that winds its way down to a calming center disk. Make them the centerpiece of that lavish kitchen sideboard.

Mirrors preserve light. Geometry explains space. Gold GETS NOTICED. Introducing our Flux Collection Mirror: A dazzling triple-ring of Bright Gold harmonized ellipticals, whose openwork design lends visual interest while allowing the color of the wall behind to remain visible. Perfect to add glam to the Powder Room. Or use several of them to burst the wall in a lofty space.

Fascinated with the invitingly low-slung furniture characteristic of Eastern and North African interiors? Come luxuriate among our stunning Pascha Series Stacking Tables: Distinctively textured and resplendent with broad flutes of lustrous Coppery metalwork, the Pascha offer the perfect combination of function, eclecticism, and sumptuousness. Imagine them in a sunken conversation pit or stowed in an antique fireplace niche, reflecting the light of a nearby luminaria.

One of the core challenges of ambitious design is the perfect coalescence of contemporary and time-honored paradigms. Presenting the Helm Marble-Top Table: A beautifully variegated crown of polished white marble supported by a slender grating of cooly urbanesque, Zinc-colored bars -- whose dynamically inward-bending silhouette comes together in an eye-pleasing basal ring. Brings traditional synthesis to a hip or eclectic design space.

Precision was to the Art Deco design movement what free-flowing contours were to its predecessor, Art Nouveau. Natural silhouettes like the ornamental rays of our beautifully handcrafted RSVP Mirror weren't just bolder and more vertical, but sharpened and repeated as though they were mass produced by early 2th Century machines. Lavish Gold finish. Perfect in the powder room.

Recognized as the stunningly intricate geometric tracery abundant in Neo-Classical and Medieval ornamentation, the Guilloche design motif offers a cosmatesque version of the sacred infinity symbols found in Ancient Eastern and Hellenic culture stories. Our Guilloche-styled Wall Mirror features a similarly elaborate radiance of graceful metal spirals and a gorgeous Bright Gold finish. Handcrafted.
